A collapsed marquee at Bellair Road near Albert Luthui Hospital in Cato Manor. DURBAN - Three children have been rushed to hospital in Durban after being injured in a tent collapse. At least 15 others had to be treated for minor injuries. READ: 72 children injured in KZN bus crash Paramedics say the tent collapsed in Bellair Road near the Cato Manor sports ground, where people were having a meeting. Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson says most of the patients were treated for minor injuries. It's believed the tent collapsed because of severe winds.